---
import Layout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---
<Layout title="Advanced Password Strength Auditor | Entropy & Brute-Force Test | DataSecureTools">
  <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: #0f172a;">
    
    <div style="width: 100%; height: 90px; background: #ffffff; border: 1px dashed #cbd5e1; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 30px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 1px;">
      ADVERTISEMENT - GOOGLE ADSENSE
    </div>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 340px; gap: 40px; align-items: start;">
      
      <main>
        <div style="background: #ffffff; border-radius: 40px; padding: 60px; box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.02); border: 1px solid #f1f5f9;">
          <header style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <span style="background: #f1f5f9; color: #475569; padding: 6px 14px; border-radius: 100px; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">Cyber Defense</span>
            <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 900; margin-top: 15px; letter-spacing: -1.5px; color: #0f172a;">Password Auditor</h1>
            <p style="color: #64748b; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-top: 15px; line-height: 1.6;">Audit your password's entropy and estimate crack time against modern brute-force clusters.</p>
          </header>

          <div style="background: #f8fafc; padding: 40px; border-radius: 24px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; margin-bottom: 35px;">
            <input type="password" id="target" placeholder="Enter password to audit..." style="width: 100%; padding: 20px 25px; border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; font-size: 1.1rem; outline: none; margin-bottom: 20px;" />
            <button id="runBtn" style="width: 100%; background: #0f172a; color: white; padding: 18px; border-radius: 16px; border: none; font-weight: 800; font-size: 1rem; cursor: pointer; transition: 0.3s; text-transform: uppercase;">AUDIT STRENGTH</button>
          </div>

          <div id="results" style="display: none; animation: slideUp 0.6s ease-out;">
              <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                  <div style="background: #ffffff; padding: 30px; border-radius: 24px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9; text-align: center;">
                      <span style="font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 800; color: #94a3b8; text-transform: uppercase;">Security Entropy</span>
                      <div id="v-entropy" style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 900; color: #10b981; margin-top: 8px;">0 Bits</div>
                  </div>
                  <div style="background: #ffffff; padding: 30px; border-radius: 24px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9; text-align: center;">
                      <span style="font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 800; color: #94a3b8; text-transform: uppercase;">Crack Time</span>
                      <div id="v-time" style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 900; color: #0f172a; margin-top: 8px;">Instantly</div>
                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <article style="margin-top: 60px; line-height: 1.8; color: #475569;">
          <h2 style="color: #0f172a; font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.5px;">The Mathematics of Password Entropy and Security</h2>
          <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Protecting your digital identity starts with understanding <strong>Information Entropy</strong>. Unlike simple character counting, entropy measures the degree of randomness in a string. Our <strong>Password Strength Auditor</strong> uses advanced algorithms to calculate the bit-strength of your credentials, providing a realistic estimate of how long it would take for a <strong>distributed brute-force cluster</strong> to crack your hash. In 2026, with the rise of AI-driven dictionary attacks, maintaining a high entropy score is the only way to safeguard your sensitive data.</p>
          
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 40px; margin-top: 40px;">
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 800; color: #0f172a; margin-bottom: 15px;">Brute-Force Resilience</h3>
                <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7;">Modern hardware can test billions of combinations per second. A password's true defense lies in its complexity and length, increasing the total permutations beyond the reach of conventional computing power.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 800; color: #0f172a; margin-bottom: 15px;">MFA Complement</h3>
                <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7;">While a strong password is a vital first layer, it should always be paired with Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) to provide a defense-in-depth security posture.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </main>

      <aside>
        <div style="width: 100%; height: 600px; background: #ffffff; border: 1px dashed #cbd5e1; border-radius: 24px; margin-bottom: 40px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.8rem; text-align: center; padding: 20px;">
          ADSENSE SKYSCRAPER
        </div>

        <div style="background: #f8fafc; border-radius: 32px; padding: 30px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 900; color: #0f172a; margin-bottom: 25px;">Security Advice</h3>
            <div style="background: #ffffff; padding: 25px; border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.01); margin-bottom: 20px; border: 1px solid #f1f5f9;">
                <strong style="color: #4f46e5; display: block; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase;">Use Passphrases</strong>
                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: #64748b; line-height: 1.6;">Four random words are often harder to crack than a short password with symbols, and much easier to remember.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="background: #ffffff; padding: 25px; border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.01); border: 1px solid #f1f5f9;">
                <strong style="color: #10b981; display: block; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase;">Vault Management</strong>
                <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: #64748b; line-height: 1.6;">Utilize zero-knowledge password managers to store complex, unique credentials for every single account you own.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style> @keyframes slideUp { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } } </style>

<script>
  const btn = document.getElementById('runBtn');
  btn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const pwd = (document.getElementById('target') as HTMLInputElement).value;
    if(!pwd) return alert("Enter password");

    // Real Entropy Engine
    const pool = new Set(pwd.split('')).size;
    const entropy = Math.round(pwd.length * Math.log2(pool || 1));
    
    let time = "Centuries";
    if(entropy < 30) time = "Minutes";
    else if(entropy < 50) time = "Days";
    else if(entropy < 80) time = "Years";

    document.getElementById('v-entropy').innerText = entropy + " Bits";
    document.getElementById('v-entropy').style.color = entropy > 60 ? '#10b981' : '#ef4444';
    document.getElementById('v-time').innerText = time;
    
    document.getElementById('results').style.display = "block";
  });
</script>